        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 1:54PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Showers and thunderstorm are actively developing over the higher
terrain of Southwest, Central, and portions of North Central
Montana early this afternoon. These activity will be capable of
producing heavy rainfall, especially initially as showers and
storms remain anchored to the higher terrain, along with gusty
winds, small hail, and frequent lightning with the strongest
thunderstorms. If you are outdoors keep and eye to the sky and be
prepared to seek shelter. Be aware of your surroundings,
especially if low-lying areas prone to flooding or debris flows.
</description>
